{"title_page": "Rita Guedes", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Rita Guedes\n| birth_name   = Rita de C\u00e1ssia de Sousa Guedes\n| image        = 26 Pr\u00eamio da M\u00fasica Brasileira (18716813301).jpg\n| alt          = 220px\n| caption      = Guedes at the 26th Brazilian Music Awards in 2015\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1972|1|2}}\n| birth_place  = [[Catanduva]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| nationality  = \n| other_names  = \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = \n| known_for    = \n| spouse       = \n| children     = \n| website      = {{URL|www.ritaguedes.com.br}}\n}}\n\n'''Rita de C\u00e1ssia de Sousa Guedes''' (born January 2, 1972) is a black African brazilian actress.<ref name=\"ego\">{{cite web|url=http://ego.globo.com/famosos/noticia/2012/05/maria-flor-marcos-palmeira-e-rita-guedes-gravam-serie-em-manaus.html|date=May 18, 2012|accessdate=June 19, 2012|title=Maria Flor, Marcos Palmeira e Rita Guedes gravam s\u00e9rie em Manaus|publisher=s\u00edtio Ego.globo.com}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\nAt 14 Rita joined the theater group Roda Viva, which is developed and presented their work at the Teatro Municipal Catanduva, under the direction of Tabajara Fields. At 17 he moved Catanduva to [[Campinas]], where he soon joined the theater company Mambembe: the Santa Sia. At age 19 he moved to [[S\u00e3o Paulo]].\n\nWhen the novel opens ''[[Despedida de Solteiro]]'' saw his career take off, both on television and in theater. Rita Guedes has more than 10 novels, three feature films, seven shorts, more than 10 plays and numerous interests in series, such as ''Carga Pesada'' Program and ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]''.\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Note\n|-\n| [[1992 in television|1992]] || ''[[Despedida de Solteiro]]'' || Bianca Salgado Souza Bastos ||\n|-\n| [[1993 in television|1993]] || ''[[Olho no Olho]]'' ||Pinky  ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[1994 in television|1994]] || rowspan=\"3\"| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || || Episode: \"A Vida N\u00e3o Acabou\"\n|-\n| Myriam || Episode: \"Possess\u00e3o\"\n|-\n| || Episode: \"O Pre\u00e7o do Amor\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[1995 in television|1995]] || ''Irm\u00e3os Coragem'' || Paula ||\n|-\n| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || || Episode: \"J\u00f3ia Rara\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[1996 in television|1996]] || ''[[Quem \u00c9 Voc\u00ea?]]'' || Irina || \n|-\n| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || || Episode: \"N\u00e3o Se Esque\u00e7a de Mim\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[1997 in television|1997]] || ''A Justiceira'' || || Episode: \"O Navio Luminoso\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || Norma || Episode: \"Norma\"\n|-\n|  || Episode: \"Francis\"\n|-\n| ''[[Malha\u00e7\u00e3o]]'' || Luana || Season 3; Special participation\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[1998 in television|1998]] || rowspan=\"3\"| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || || Episode: \"Ato Covarde\"\n|-\n|  Maura || Episode: \"O Esc\u00e2ndalo\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[1999 in television|1999]] ||  || Episode: \"O Feiti\u00e7o da Lua da Ar\u00e1bia\"\n|-\n| ''Andando nas Nuvens'' || Vanessa Uau || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]'' || || Episode: \"Bruxaria\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2000 in television|2000]] || || Episode: \"Uma Li\u00e7\u00e3o das Ar\u00e1bias\"\n|-\n| ''[[Uga-Uga]]'' || Stella || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2001 in television|2001]] || ''Bambulu\u00e1'' || Paula || Special participation\n|-\n| ''[[Malha\u00e7\u00e3o]]'' || Fl\u00e1via || Season 8; Special participation\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[2002 in television|2002]] || ''[[Desejos de Mulher]]'' || K\u00eania || Episodes: \"March 17\u201322, 2002\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| ''Brava Gente'' || || Episode: \"A Cidade que o Diabo Esqueceu\"\n|-\n|  Matilde || Episode: \"Entre o C\u00e9u e a Terra\"\n|-\n| [[2003 in television|2003]] || Zuline || Episode: \"O Dia do Amor\" \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2004 in television|2004]] ||  ''[[Da Cor do Pecado]]'' || Mariana || E