 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Catanduva]]\n[[Category:Brazilian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Brazilian stage actresses]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriates in the United States]]\n\n{{Brazil-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Rita Guedes\n| birth_name   = Rita de C\u00e1ssia de Sousa Guedes\n| image        = 26 Pr\u00eamio da M\u00fasica Brasileira (18716813301).jpg\n| alt          = 220px\n| caption      = Guedes at the 26th Brazilian Music Awards in 2015\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1972|1|2}}\n| birth_place  = [[Catanduva]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| nationality  = \n| other_names  = \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = \n| known_for    = \n| spouse       = \n| children     = \n| website      = {{URL|www.ritaguedes.com.br}}\n}}\n\n'''Rita de C\u00e1ssia de Sousa Guedes''' (born January 2, 1972) is a [[Brazil]]ian actress.<ref name=\"ego\">{{cite web|url=http://ego.globo.com/famosos/noticia/2012/05/maria-flor-marcos-palmeira-e-rita-guedes-gravam-serie-em-manaus.html|date=May 18, 2012|accessdate=June 19, 2012|title=Maria Flor, Marcos Palmeira e Rita Guedes gravam s\u00e9rie em Manaus|publisher=s\u00edtio Ego.globo.com}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\nAt 14 Rita joined the theater group Roda Viva, which is developed and presented their work at the Teatro Municipal Catanduva, under the direction of Tabajara Fields. At 17 he moved Catanduva to [[Campinas]], where he soon joined the theater company Mambembe: the Santa Sia. At age 19 he moved to [[S\u00e3o Paulo]].\n\nWhen the novel opens ''[[Despedida de Solteiro]]'' saw his career take off, both on television and in theater. Rita Guedes has more than 10 novels, three feature films, seven shorts, more than 10 plays and numerous interests in series, such as ''Carga Pesada'' Program and ''[[Voc\u00ea Decide]]''.\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\